info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 20 at 1:58PM PST until January 21 at 3:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TO 3 PM PST SATURDAY... * WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected. * WHERE...North Coast and Central Coast zones. * WHEN...From 9 AM to 3 PM PST Saturday. * IMPACTS...Minor coastal flooding due to tidal overflow is expected around high tide. This may lead to flooding of parking lots, parks, and roads, with only isolated road closures expected. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Inundation of up to 0.5 feet above ground level is possible along shorelines and low-lying coastal areas.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property. Inundation above ground level refers to the height above the Mean Higher High Water (MHHW) level.
